Text: How many days should I have between my periods
Message JSON: {"userId":"51a71c3d-bd50-4bc3-977f-6c448f812e26","text":"How many days should I have between my periods "}

Text: Our bodies are all different! Most women get their period once a month, around the same time. But for other women, their periods come once every couple of months. It's possible that once in awhile you might have two periods in one month. But it doesn't matter how often you get you period - you can still get pregnant at any time. This is why a lot of women use birth control to regulate their periods. If your period is abnormal or you have concerns, definitely talk to a doctor.
